---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<BaseLayout title="Bylaws" description="Official bylaws and governance structure of the Scandinavian Hard Dance Alliance.">
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Bylaws & Governance</h1>
      <p class="lead">Official statutes governing the Scandinavian Hard Dance Alliance</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="bylaws-content">
        <div class="document-notice">
          <p>
            <!-- TODO: Update with actual founding date and legal information -->
            <strong>Note:</strong> These bylaws were adopted on [DATE] and last amended on [DATE].
            This is a simplified English translation for accessibility. Official Swedish version
            available upon request.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Article 1: Name and Purpose -->
        <article class="bylaw-article">
          <h2>Article 1: Name and Purpose</h2>

          <h3>§1.1 Name</h3>
          <p>
            <!-- TODO: Update with official registered name if different -->
            The name of the organization is "Scandinavian Hard Dance Alliance" (SHDA).
          </p>

          <h3>§1.2 Purpose</h3>
          <p>
            The purpose of SHDA is to:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Promote and develop the hard dance music scene across Scandinavia</li>
            <li>Facilitate collaboration between hard dance event organizers and related companies</li>
            <li>Support member organizations through resource sharing and knowledge exchange</li>
            <li>Strengthen the Scandinavian hard dance community through networking and joint initiatives</li>
            <li>Maintain high standards of quality and safety in hard dance events</li>
            <li>Foster growth driven by passion for music rather than purely commercial interests</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>§1.3 Geographical Scope</h3>
          <p>
            SHDA primarily operates within and serves the Scandinavian countries:
            Sweden, Denmark, Norway, and Finland.
          </p>
        </article>

        <!-- Article 2: Membership -->
        <article class="bylaw-article">
          <h2>Article 2: Membership</h2>

          <h3>§2.1 Eligibility</h3>
          <p>
            Membership is open to:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Event organizers focused on hard dance genres (hardstyle, hardcore, rawstyle, frenchcore, hardtechno)</li>
            <li>Companies providing services to the hard dance community (travel, production, etc.)</li>
            <li>Organizations based in or primarily operating within Scandinavian countries</li>
            <li>Entities demonstrating commitment to the alliance's values and purpose</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>§2.2 Application Process</h3>
          <p>
            <!-- TODO: Define actual application process -->
            Prospective members must submit an application to the board including:
            organization details, proof of activities in the hard dance scene, and endorsement
            from at least one current member. The board reviews applications quarterly.
          </p>

          <h3>§2.3 Membership Rights</h3>
          <p>
            Members have the right to:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Participate in all quarterly meetings</li>
            <li>Access shared resources and facilities</li>
            <li>Participate in collaborative bookings and events</li>
            <li>Vote on alliance matters (one vote per member organization)</li>
            <li>Use SHDA affiliation in marketing materials</li>
            <li>Propose initiatives and agenda items for meetings</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>§2.4 Membership Obligations</h3>
          <p>
            Members are expected to:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Attend or be represented at quarterly meetings</li>
            <li>Pay annual membership fees as determined by the annual meeting</li>
            <li>Uphold the values and standards of the alliance</li>
            <li>Contribute to resource sharing and collaboration</li>
            <li>Support fellow members when possible</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>§2.5 Termination of Membership</h3>
          <p>
            Membership may be terminated by member resignation or board decision in cases of
            repeated violation of bylaws, failure to meet obligations, or actions harmful to
            the alliance reputation. Members may appeal termination decisions to the annual meeting.
          </p>
        </article>

        <!-- Article 3: Governance -->
        <article class="bylaw-article">
          <h2>Article 3: Governance Structure</h2>

          <h3>§3.1 Board Composition</h3>
          <p>
            <!-- TODO: Define actual board structure -->
            The alliance is governed by a board consisting of:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Chairperson</li>
            <li>Vice Chairperson</li>
            <li>Treasurer</li>
            <li>Secretary</li>
            <li>2-4 Board Members at Large</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>§3.2 Board Elections</h3>
          <p>
            Board members are elected at the annual meeting for two-year terms. Elections are
            staggered to ensure continuity. All member organizations may nominate candidates
            and vote in elections.
          </p>

          <h3>§3.3 Board Responsibilities</h3>
          <p>
            The board is responsible for:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Day-to-day management of alliance affairs</li>
            <li>Processing membership applications</li>
            <li>Managing alliance finances and resources</li>
            <li>Organizing quarterly meetings and annual meeting</li>
            <li>Implementing decisions from annual meetings</li>
            <li>Representing the alliance externally</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>§3.4 Decision Making</h3>
          <p>
            Board decisions require simple majority unless otherwise specified in these bylaws.
            In case of tie, the chairperson has the deciding vote. Board meetings require at
            least half of board members present to constitute a quorum.
          </p>
        </article>

        <!-- Article 4: Meetings -->
        <article class="bylaw-article">
          <h2>Article 4: Meetings</h2>

          <h3>§4.1 Annual Meeting</h3>
          <p>
            <!-- TODO: Set actual annual meeting schedule -->
            The annual meeting shall be held each year in Q4. Notice must be provided to all
            members at least 30 days in advance. The annual meeting:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Reviews the previous year's activities and finances</li>
            <li>Elects board members</li>
            <li>Sets membership fees for the coming year</li>
            <li>Decides on major initiatives and policy changes</li>
            <li>Amends bylaws (requires 2/3 majority)</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>§4.2 Quarterly Meetings</h3>
          <p>
            Quarterly meetings are held four times per year, rotating between member countries.
            These meetings focus on operational matters, collaboration planning, and knowledge
            sharing. All members are encouraged to attend.
          </p>

          <h3>§4.3 Extraordinary Meetings</h3>
          <p>
            Extraordinary meetings may be called by the board or upon written request of at least
            one-third of member organizations. Notice must be provided at least 14 days in advance.
          </p>
        </article>

        <!-- Article 5: Finances -->
        <article class="bylaw-article">
          <h2>Article 5: Finances</h2>

          <h3>§5.1 Funding</h3>
          <p>
            <!-- TODO: Define actual fee structure -->
            Alliance operations are funded through:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Annual membership fees</li>
            <li>Event collaboration revenues (if applicable)</li>
            <li>Sponsorships and partnerships</li>
            <li>Other income approved by the board</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>§5.2 Financial Management</h3>
          <p>
            The treasurer is responsible for managing alliance finances. Annual financial
            statements must be presented at the annual meeting. The alliance operates on a
            non-profit basis with any surplus reinvested in alliance activities.
          </p>

          <h3>§5.3 Audit</h3>
          <p>
            Alliance accounts shall be audited annually by an external auditor or auditors
            appointed at the annual meeting.
          </p>
        </article>

        <!-- Article 6: Amendments and Dissolution -->
        <article class="bylaw-article">
          <h2>Article 6: Amendments and Dissolution</h2>

          <h3>§6.1 Bylaw Amendments</h3>
          <p>
            These bylaws may be amended at an annual or extraordinary meeting with a two-thirds
            majority vote of member organizations present. Proposed amendments must be included
            in the meeting notice.
          </p>

          <h3>§6.2 Dissolution</h3>
          <p>
            The alliance may be dissolved by a two-thirds majority vote at an annual meeting,
            confirmed by a similar vote at an extraordinary meeting held at least 3 months later.
            Upon dissolution, remaining assets shall be distributed to organizations or initiatives
            supporting hard dance music in Scandinavia, as determined by the final meeting.
          </p>
        </article>

        <!-- Document Info -->
        <div class="document-footer">
          <h3>Document Information</h3>
          <p>
            <!-- TODO: Update with actual dates and signatures -->
            <strong>Adopted:</strong> [Date]<br>
            <strong>Last Amended:</strong> [Date]<br>
            <strong>Next Review:</strong> [Date]
          </p>
          <p>
            For questions about these bylaws or governance matters, please <a href={`${base}/kontakt`}>contact the board</a>.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Board Section -->
        <div class="board-section">
          <h2>Current Board Members</h2>
          <p>
            <!-- TODO: Add actual board member names and organizations -->
          </p>
          <div class="board-grid">
            <div class="board-member">
              <h4>Chairperson</h4>
              <p>[Name]</p>
              <p class="organization">[Organization]</p>
            </div>
            <div class="board-member">
              <h4>Vice Chairperson</h4>
              <p>[Name]</p>
              <p class="organization">[Organization]</p>
            </div>
            <div class="board-member">
              <h4>Treasurer</h4>
              <p>[Name]</p>
              <p class="organization">[Organization]</p>
            </div>
            <div class="board-member">
              <h4>Secretary</h4>
              <p>[Name]</p>
              <p class="organization">[Organization]</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-hero {
    padding: var(--spacing-4xl) 0 var(--spacing-2xl);
    text-align: center;
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, var(--color-bg-primary) 0%, var(--color-bg-secondary) 100%);
  }

  .page-hero h1 {
    font-size: 3.5rem;
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
  }

  .page-hero .lead {
    color: var(--color-accent-cyan);
    font-size: 1.25rem;
  }

  .bylaws-content {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .document-notice {
    background-color: var(--color-bg-secondary);
    border-left: 4px solid var(--color-accent-orange);
    padding: var(--spacing-lg);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-4xl);
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
  }

  .document-notice p {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  }

  .bylaw-article {
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-4xl);
    padding-bottom: var(--spacing-2xl);
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(0, 240, 255, 0.1);
  }

  .bylaw-article:last-of-type {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .bylaw-article h2 {
    color: var(--color-accent-cyan);
    font-size: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xl);
  }

  .bylaw-article h3 {
    color: var(--color-text-white);
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    margin-top: var(--spacing-xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
  }

  .bylaw-article p {
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
  }

  .bylaw-article ul {
    margin-left: var(--spacing-xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-lg);
  }

  .bylaw-article li {
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-sm);
  }

  .document-footer {
    background-color: var(--color-bg-secondary);
    padding: var(--spacing-xl);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    margin-top: var(--spacing-4xl);
  }

  .document-footer h3 {
    color: var(--color-accent-cyan);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
  }

  .document-footer p {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
  }

  .document-footer p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .board-section {
    margin-top: var(--spacing-4xl);
    padding-top: var(--spacing-4xl);
    border-top: 2px solid rgba(0, 240, 255, 0.2);
  }

  .board-section h2 {
    color: var(--color-accent-cyan);
    font-size: 2rem;
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-2xl);
  }

  .board-section > p {
    text-align: center;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xl);
  }

  .board-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--spacing-xl);
  }

  .board-member {
    background-color: var(--color-bg-secondary);
    padding: var(--spacing-lg);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    text-align: center;
    border: 1px solid rgba(0, 240, 255, 0.2);
  }

  .board-member h4 {
    color: var(--color-accent-cyan);
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-sm);
  }

  .board-member p {
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xs);
  }

  .board-member .organization {
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .page-hero h1 {
      font-size: 2.5rem;
    }

    .board-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
